[[File:Tunisia_sw_locations.png|thumb|right|250px|A map of Tunisia annotated with ''Star Wars'' filming locations]]
'''Tunisia''' is a country in North Africa. Locations in Tunisia were used to film scenes for the first six ''[[Star Wars]]'' movies except [[Star Wars: Episode V The Empire Strikes Back|''Star Wars'': Episode V ''The Empire Strikes Back]].

{{Stub}}

The main locations are:
*[[Chott el Jerid]] &mdash; exterior of the [[Lars homestead]].
*[[Djerba]] ([[Sidi Jemour]] and [[Ajim]])&mdash; [[Ben Kenobi's home]], [[Mos Eisley]] and the deleted scenes set in [[Anchorhead]] ([[Star Wars: Episode IV A New Hope|''Star Wars'': Episode IV ''A New Hope'']]).
*[[Grand Dune]] &mdash; the [[Dune Sea]] where [[R2-D2]] and [[C-3PO]] crash in Episode IV. Nefta was also in this area.
*[[Hôtel Sidi Driss]] &mdash; the interior of the Lars homestead.
*[[Ksar Hadada]], [[Ksar Medenine]] and [[Ksar Ouled Soltane]] &mdash; the [[Slave Quarters Row]].
*[[Oung Jmel]] &mdash; a rock seen in [[Star Wars: Episode I The Phantom Menace|''Star Wars'': Episode I ''The Phantom Menace]] and [[Star Wars: Episode II Attack of the Clones|''Star Wars'': Episode II ''Attack of the Clones'']], especially for [[Mos Espa]].
*[[Sidi Bouhlel]] &mdash; the canyon where [[Luke Skywalker]] meets [[Obi-Wan Kenobi|Ben Kenobi]] in Episode IV.

